<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-04-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Barrett</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-04-07"><hi rend="italic">April 7,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis instructs Mr. Barrett to ask the Government of Panama whether
                            our diplomatic and consular representatives may exercise their good
                            offices, when occasion requires, in behalf of Chinese subjects as
                            requested by the Chinese Government.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>